2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   ## Root cause
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   `AsciiJSON.Render` in `render/json.go` escapes every rune above `unicode.MaxASCII` with `fmt.Appendf(escapeBuf[:0], "\\u%04x", r)`. The `%04x` verb only sets a **minimum** width of four hex digits, not a fixed width. Code points above U+FFFF (supplementary planes: emoji, many rare scripts) need five or six hex digits in a single `\u` token, producing invalid JSON escapes such as `\u1f600` instead of the RFC 8259 §7 UTF-16 surrogate pair `\ud83d\ude00`.
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   Decoders treat `\u` as exactly four hex digits, so the extra digit(s) become literal characters. The JSON remains syntactically valid, so the corruption is silent and does not round-trip.
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   BMP characters (U+0080–U+FFFF), including the existing test case `GO语言`, are unaffected because they always fit in four hex digits.
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   ## Proposed fix
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   Change only the non-ASCII escaping branch in `AsciiJSON.Render`:
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   1. **BMP (r ≤ 0xFFFF):** Keep current behavior — emit a single `\u%04x` escape (four lowercase hex digits, matching existing output style).
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   2. **Non-BMP (r > 0xFFFF):** Per RFC 8259, encode as a UTF-16 surrogate pair:
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |      - `hi = 0xD800 + ((r - 0x10000) >> 10)`
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |      - `lo = 0xDC00 + ((r - 0x10000) & 0x3FF)`
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |      - Emit `\u%04x\u%04x` for `hi` and `lo`.
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   Use `unicode/utf16.EncodeRune` (stdlib, same semantics) or equivalent inline math; branch on `r > 0xFFFF` for the second escape, not on the low return value alone (BMP returns a dummy second value).
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   3. **Buffer sizing:** Update `escapeBuf` capacity from 6 to **12** bytes (`\uXXXX\uYYYY`) and adjust the comment accordingly.
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   No changes to `Context.AsciiJSON`, content-type handling, marshaling, or other JSON renderers.
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   **Assumption:** Input is valid UTF-8 from `json.API.Marshal` + `bytesconv.BytesToString`; invalid/lone surrogate runes are out of scope (marshal output should not contain them).
2026-06-04 13:55:14,355 | DEBUG    |   
