2026-06-04 13:57:34,660 | DEBUG    |   ## Root cause
2026-06-04 13:57:34,660 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:57:34,660 | DEBUG    |   `AsciiJSON.Render` in `render/json.go` escapes every rune above `unicode.MaxASCII` with `fmt.Appendf(escapeBuf[:0], "\\u%04x", r)`. The `%04x` verb only sets a **minimum** width of four hex digits, not a fixed width. Code points above U+FFFF (supplementary planes: emoji, many rare scripts) need five or six hex digits in a single `\u` token, producing invalid JSON escapes such as `\u1f600` instead of the RFC 8259 
